        <h1 id="title">Ip Man</h1>
        <p>The man who trained Bruce Lee</p>
        <figure>
            <img id="image" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Yip_Man.jpg/220px-Yip_Man.jpg" alt="A portrait of Ip Man left and Bruce Lee on the right"/>
            <figcaption id="image-caption">Ip Man, left, the master of Wing Chun who  trained Bruce Lee before he moved to the USA however he is famous for more.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <section id="tribute-info">
            <h3>Here's a timeline of Ip Man's life:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>1893</strong>
                    - Born in Foshan
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1906</strong>
                    - Ip Man begins training in Wing Chun
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1909</strong>
                    - Moved to Hong Kong
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1916</strong>
                    - Married Cheung Wing-sing and returned to Foshan
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1937</strong>
                    - Moved to Kwok Fu during second Sino-Japanese War
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1950</strong>
                    - Family returned to Hong Kong, but due to the border closure Ip and his family were seperated.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1960</strong>
                    - Official Wing Chun assosciation is created
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1972</strong>
                    - Ip Man passes away
                </li>
            </ul>
            <blockquote>
                <p>"We all have innder demons to fight, we call these demons, fear, and hatred and anger. If you do not conquer them then a life of one hundred years is a tragedy. If you do then a life of a single day is a triumph."</p>
                <cite>-- Ip Man</cite>
            </blockquote>
            <h3>
                 If you have time, feel free to read up more about this amazing human being on <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ip_Man">Wikipedia</a>
            </h3>
        </section>
